1.Write a Java program to print elements of an array in reverse order.
import java.util.Scanner;

class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        // Size of array
        int n = sc.nextInt();

        int[] arr = new int[n];

        // Input array elements
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {

            arr[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        // Print array in reverse order
        for(int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {

            System.out.print(arr[i] + " ");
        }
    }
}
O/p:
4
10
20
30
40
40 30 20 10

2.Create an array of five floats and calculate their sum
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        // Create float array
        float[] numbers = {1.2f, 2.5f, 3.1f, 4.8f, 5.4f};

